Here's a radical proposal for implementation of a Duel-Based ranking system:<br>
<br>
First, I suggest we keep records and standing with an ELO-style K-Value rating system.  I'm <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> very open</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to redefining the K-Value for certain types of events, or the criteria used in my example; but I'd be much more apt to participate if we used a system similar to below.<br>
<br>
All players have a starting Rating of (1000+(Level*10))<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> KValue</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> = Arbitrary assignment for the quality of event.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Scoring Points</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> = 0 for loss, 1 for win, .5 for draw<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Win Probability</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  = 1 / (10*((Opponent's Rating - Player's Rating)/400)+1)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Player's New Rating</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> = Player's Rating + (KValue*(Scoring Points - Win Probability)<br>
<br>
The K-Value for a particular event can be set based on pre-determined criteria and should range from 4-40 (The K-Value of an event determines roughly the number of points that can shift hands in a single duel.)<br>
Results in dispute are scored with 0 scoring points for BOTH players.<br>
<br>
4 - 1 criteria met<br>
8 - 2 criteria met<br>
12 - 3 criteria met<br>
26 - 4 criteria met<br>
24 - 5 criteria met<br>
32 - all 6 criteria met<br>
36 - all 6 criteria met and reserved for special events<br>
40 - all 6 criteria met and reserved for championships, invitations<br>
<br>
Criteria for point qualifications:<br>
(1) Witnessed by bystanders, all rules followed, results reported in a timely fashion.<br>
(2) Public invited to participate with 24 hours notice.<br>
(3) At least 4 participants in round-robin, Swiss, or luck of the draw.<br>
(4) At least 4 ADDITIONAL participants in round-robin, Swiss, or luck of the draw.<br>
(5) An &quot;official&quot; oversees the match (also counts as a spectator witness - see (1))<br>
(6) Public invited to participate with 7 days notice (tenically 2 criteria, see (2))<br>
<br>
